12 "§ 77-89.3. Terms of members.Membership; terms of office; eligibility for appointment.
13 (a) Upon its creation, the Commission shall have has a governing board of five
14 commissioners. Except as otherwise provided for the first five-year period, each commissioner
15 shall serve a five-year term, with commissioners to serve overlapping terms so that one
16 commissioner appointment is made each year. Upon creation of the Commission, the board of
17 Catawba County shall appoint two commissioners and the boards of the other three counties shall
18 appoint one each. These initial appointees shall serve until September 30 following their
19 appointment. Thereafter, appointments shall be made each October 1 by the respective boards of
20 the four counties as follows:comprised of members appointed in accordance with subsections (b)
21 and (c) of this section.
22 (1) First year: Commissioner from Catawba, one-year term; commissioner from
23 Iredell, two-year term; commissioner from Lincoln, three-year term;
24 commissioner from Mecklenburg, four-year term; commissioner from
25 Catawba, five-year term.
26 (2) Second year: Commissioner from Iredell, five-year term.
27 (3) Third year: Commissioner from Lincoln, five-year term.
28 (4) Fourth year: Commissioner from Mecklenburg, five-year term.
29 (5) Fifth year: Commissioner from Catawba, five-year term.
30 (6) Sixth and succeeding years: appointments for five-year terms in rotation by
31 county in the order set out above.
32 (b) For the initial appointments, each participating local government shall appoint one
33 commissioner to serve a four-year term and a second commissioner to serve a five-year term.
34 Except as otherwise provided for the initial appointments, each commissioner shall serve a
35 five-year term.
36 (c) Those commissioners appointed by participating local governments in accordance
37 with subsection (b) of this section shall appoint one commissioner to a five-year term who shall
38 serve a one-year term as chair of the Commission. Each succeeding four years, the Commission
39 shall elect a new chair from the current commissioners to serve a one-year term. At the end of
40 each fourth year, the commissioners appointed by participating local governments in accordance
41 with subsection (b) of this section shall repeat the process of electing a chair as provided in this
42 subsection.
43 (d) Participating local governments shall appoint individuals who possess one or more of
44 the following qualifications:
45 (1) Has a primary residence adjoining Lake Norman.
46 (2) Has knowledge of boater safety protocols for all types of vessels.
47 (3) Has knowledge of water quality and aquatic vegetation management.
48 (4) Has experience in law enforcement.
49 (5) Has experience in public recreation management.
50 (6) Has experience in wildlife resources management.
