4 even-numbered years. The term of a person appointed to the commission pursuant to subdivision
5 (6) of subsection (a) of this section shall expire expires on 1 January of odd-numbered years. The
6 term of a member who is appointed to the commissions pursuant to subdivisions (5) and (11) of
7 subsection (a) and subdivisions (5) and (6) of subsection (b) of this section shall serve as provided
8 by the General Assembly of South Carolina. An appointment to fill a vacancy on the commissions
9 shall be for the unexpired portion of the term. A vacancy on the commissions shall be filled in
10 the same manner as the original appointment. Members of the commissions who are appointed
11 from or reside in North Carolina may be removed by the Governor of North Carolina for
12 misfeasance, malfeasance, or nonfeasance, as provided in G.S. 143B-13.
13 …
14 (f) Each commission shall meet upon the call of the Chair. A majority of each
15 commission shall constitute constitutes a quorum for the transaction of business.
16 …."
17 SECTION 4.(a) Any joint resolution adopted by the four counties pursuant to
18 Chapter 1089 of the 1969 Session Laws, that is in effect immediately prior to the effective date
19 of this act, shall expire upon the adoption of a subsequent joint resolution by the participating
20 local governments consistent with the provisions of this act or September 30, 2025, whichever is
21 earlier.
22 SECTION 4.(b) The terms of the commissioners currently appointed to the
23 governing board of the Lake Norman Marine Commission shall expire on September 30, 2025.
24 SECTION 5. Upon the Lake Norman Marine Commission being reconstituted
25 pursuant to a joint resolution adopted by the participating local governments, all new
26 appointments to the governing board of the Lake Norman Marine Commission will be effective
27 on October 1, 2025.
28 SECTION 6. All rules, regulations, and decisions made by the predecessor Lake
29 Norman Marine Commission, reconstituted in accordance with this act, shall remain in full force
30 and effect until and unless duly modified by the successor entity.
31 SECTION 7. Except as otherwise provided, this act is effective when it becomes
32 law.
